<br>
The problem though is the loot is not good at all. There are no humanistic mobs (skellys, orcs, kobolds, etc.--oh, and bixies just don't count!!!!), so there is no coin being dropped and not items.  Most other zones have some kind of decaying skelly and low level mobs that carry weapons, shields, armor or bags and occasional other good stuff.  <br>
<br>
Everyone rags on SF as a starting zone-- yes, it's more dangerous, but i made bank at newbie levels on spiderling silk (plenty of spiderlings--um... maybe too many) and cracked staves i got from decay skellies.  Kobold camps aren't too high either, and the weaker ones still can drop (or did way back when at least) bags and armor.<br>
<br>
GFay would be the best if it wasn't so crowded.  TONS of orcs of varying levels which drop coin, weapons, shields, and lots of armor to wear or sell.  Plus it's still got spiders and wolves for your tailoring needs.  <br>
<br>
Just my toughts...<br>
<br>
